{"title": "Order Reborn", "content": "\"Speak again the ancient oaths and return to men the Shards they once bore. The Knights Radiant must stand again.\"\n\nLong ago, there existed an order of people who battled evil valiantly but have since fallen into disarray and were ultimately forgotten. But as the ancient evil rises its head again, a new group of heroes will take up the fallen banner of their ancestors and defend the world that they passed down to them in their name.\n\nThe Order Reborn is a reincarnation of an extinct heroic organization that has been forgotten over time but resurrected by the distant successors to combat evil, new or old. It is probably based on the old principles but (ideally) with adjustments made to prevent it from meeting the same end.\n\nUsually precipitated by the Last of His Kind, who will become The Mentor. The \"order\" being rebuilt is often The Chosen Many. A subtrope of The Order. Compare with Putting the Band Back Together. For this trope on nation-wide scale, see Resurgent Empire.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrderReborn", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheStormlightArchive", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Voltron", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheDCU", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Shadowpact", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/TheTempest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/GulliversTravels", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheScarletPimpernel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarWarsLegends", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LoneWolf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/InheritanceCycle", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Deryni", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheHistoryOfTheGalaxy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ASongOfIceAndFire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/KindlingAshes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheStormlightArchive", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WordsOfRadiance", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBeastArises", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Andromed